title: One of the best games on mobile
body:
OPTC is not only one of the best designed games on the App Store, but one of the most densely packed and massively fun games I've ever played on mobile. There's always new things going on in game and even with the time based "wait to play" gameplay, I still find myself enjoying the experience more than any other similar game I've played.

It is possible to pay to win or "be better", but it actually takes skill and planning to play this game well, especially later in the game. OPTC has "rainbow gems" which are considered the premier currency worth real world money. USE THEM WELL. 

I am lv 986 in this game having played for over 1700 days. I cannot say enough about how much fun this game is. So pick it up and try it for yourself.

title: Lag time in reporting accuracy
body: I live in Florida so keeping tabs on hurricanes is very important. The problem I have is that this app is several hours behind in reporting hurricane trajectory forecast info. I may check it just before bed and notice that this app reports something totally different than the weather channel and the local news and then wake up 8 hours later and find out that this app has changed to reflect what the news stations say. Weâ€™re talking about several hundred mile distances here. And this happens all the time. If the app reflected CURRENT data on hurricanes Iâ€™d give it 5 stars.

title: Magic Comes with a Price Dearie
body:
I have been playing this game from the beginning and I love this game, Gameloft does a really good job capturing stories and moments with the characters along with creating things similar to the attractions at the park. I also really enjoy the music which feels like you are at the parks or with the characters; truly magical for sure!

However this game has become really REALLY expensive over time. And unfortunately it is impossible to gain as much magic in order to level up or buy attractions and still be able to hoard magic .. itâ€™s quite unfortunate actually cause it really puts a strain on whether to use real money or not. I wish it was more like before because now I have to really wait for days or maybe weeks to even save enough magic to gain something extra or increase my XP. If you are willing to use money no problem, then this game is perfect but for those who prefer to keep real and virtual money separate, you might not move anywhere in the game.

title: Voice Recognition is Horrible
body:
Iâ€™ve heard great things about Babbel. At least I thought I had, but then I realized after buying a Spanish lesson that all of those positive reviews were from their ads, not from people who had actually used it.

I was excited to relearn Spanish after years of not using it, thinking this would be a great refresher. Unfortunately, I am already regretting my purchase. Not only is my lesson extremely basic given I entered intermediate as my level, the voice recognition is so frustrating Iâ€™m losing motivation. 

I was fluent in Spanish years ago so know how to say the basic phrases covered in the first several lessons, but despite my repeated attempts Iâ€™m continuously told Iâ€™m wrong. Trust me, I know how to say â€œellos and ellasâ€ I lived in Peru for a year. Thanks for wasting my time and money, Babbel. Never again.

title: Low-Key Platform
body:
I joined Curtsy last June. Iâ€™ve made a number of sales and purchases.

Compared to my experiences on Poshmark, Mercari, and Tradesy, the Curtsy platform is much more low-key. That said, I really like their customer service. They are very responsive and friendly. I feel like they care about my experience.

Lately Iâ€™ve developed a couple concerns though. 

Iâ€™ve reported a number of obvious counterfeit listings. These listings are described as authentic but are replicas or inspired products that can be easily found for wholesale purchase online. Iâ€™ve yet to see a reported listing removed. If Curtsy is allowing the sale of counterfeit items, I feel the least they can do is require that sellers acknowledge that the listings are not authentic.

Secondly, I recently purchased an item that was described as rarely used and no where in the description or photos mentioned stains and leather scuffing. After photo documenting these issues, their customer service accepted my return of the item, which was great; my issue has to do with my purchase review. Itâ€™s been removed and the seller now has a 5-star rating again. Due to this, I no longer trust their rating system.

After these experiences, Iâ€™m questioning if I really want to continue using this platform.

title: Great upgrade from 90-day plan
body:
Finished the original 90-day plan the day the app launched so downloaded immediately and began on the advanced set of cycles. Cost wise the app is great value for money for the 12 month subscription and it allows you to keep going rather than just see it as a 3 months thing and giving up. It feels very similar to those used to the 90 day plan with added features. Looking forward to the shopping list update ðŸ™ðŸ».
In general Iâ€™ve found Joeâ€™s plan easy to follow, challenging but not impossible and Iâ€™ve loved 95% of the meals, and they are MEALS, no tiny little portions here, they keep you fuelled. Want to kick start your existing routine or start from scratch and have the time for 5 x 30min workouts a week (and meal prep) I 100% recommend you sign up. I lost 8kg on the original plan, now Iâ€™m not fussed about the weight itâ€™s about getting stronger, leaner and continuing the path to balance!

title: Great concept, terrible app
body:
Love the idea but the app is covered with tech glitches all throughout the process. First it took me forever to actually sign up. For days it wouldnâ€™t even process a payment. Second, the design kept reverting back to previous edits when I went to checkout. Additionally, it would randomly swap card panels around (order wise). One screen literally was having a seizure. Those are just the glitches I remember. Ohh also I donâ€™t think the website is any better. Iâ€™m very torn whether the frustration is worth the cuteness of the result.
Concept wise Iâ€™d like to see another subscription level that actually increases the number of cards you get per month (independent of the number of panels on each). I think that would make most sense for multiple levels of subscriptions.

title: Love This App!
body:
This is an awesome app. Gives those looking for new music a place to go, and both veteran and new artists have a place to show their talent.

Bandcamp has been great for me. If I had to make a recommendation, it would be to create custom playlists that the user can drag and drop albums into. For those with extensive libraries, scrolling through album after album for that one specific song can get a bit tedious. Keep up the amazing work!

title: Watch chat
body:
I have paid for so many of these â€˜great appsâ€™ and after a while it just becomes useless. If the developer was genuine the app should be allowed free for 1 year and not just 3 days - and if it is still worth its salt I am positive the users will be happy to pay for it . Not 3 days - not 6 months but 1 year free . A good test !!!

March 3,2021
The developer of this app responded to me very promptly to the above review which gives me the comfort ( and to other users)  that they are responsive and professional.
I wish to clarify that my above review was to merely highlight to this developer NOT to fall into the trap of a short â€˜free test periodâ€™ (like others) to â€˜urgentlyâ€™ sign up a subscription. I have just signed up for this â€˜free test periodâ€™ and I am into day 1 (out of 3 days) to test the app. I personally would like to test it over a longer period. So far this app seemed to be working well unlike â€˜othersâ€™. I look forward to finally using a good app.

title: Useful application but very difficult to use
body: This could be a good application, if not a huge amount of ux bugs and mistakes.  For example, try to write a comment if a dark theme is enabled on your iPad - this is impossible, because the text is white on a white background. Or try to type a comment in several sentences, in this case the input window does not expand to fit all lines of the text, but shows only one line in insanely small font size and it becomes a nightmare to correct the text. After all this, you start to doubt whether the creators of this application have ever used their product while working on their products for designers?

title: Nice for what it does
body:
Thank you developers! Finally what I was looking for.
Better than my garmin dezl. Use it in conjunction with my Dezl just in case but so far works very well. Word of caution tho, donâ€™t entirely trust for low bridges. My Garmin Dezl and this app sends me towards a low bridge near me as well unfortunately. Better routings and finds businesses by names. Satellite view and the ability to manually set entrance pinpoints. So far, so good.
Edit: Sorry to say I had to take a star away due to that it at times wants me to reroute down small residential neighborhoods. My garmin rerouted in a safe manner. 
I think Hammer gps has a ton of potential but maybe just updates will help.

title: Where to Start
body: I canâ€™t give this game five stars nor can I give it one. It was a love-hate from the beginning when I downloaded it. Needed something to eat up some time while in the woods or boredom. The game for the most part did accomplish that. You mindlessly jump from one level to the next smashing castles. It doesnâ€™t take long and youâ€™re completing dozens of levels and soon itâ€™s 100â€™s before you know it. The game successfully ate up some time I was trying to pass. However, the game also ate up huge chunks of my battery while playing too. Many of the levels seem to closely resemble other levels and castles with perhaps the â€œcameraâ€ angle or your viewing angle being moved around slightly... but nonetheless the levels were different. My main problem outside of the battery depletion was ads. I would love to know what these companies make off ads.(these guys are the only ones with annoying ads) It seemed that when I first started playing they were not originally bad but progressively worsened in number of ads and duration. Then I turned off cellular data for the app and amazingly the ads disappeared. I was very excited with exception of the battery life of course. Then after not playing for a while, I got back in the game, played a few levels with no ads, and then the ads started all over again. I went in and checked my cellular settings and there was the data privilege removed yet ads were coming in per normal (I was up on a mtn with any WiFi being miles away.) This was the final straw for me. Ad heaven and if the game could supersede what privileges I gave it, what else would it do, or information would it use....

title: Duplicated order, can only cancel on website!
body:
First off, it duplicated a three digit order and placed both. Secondly, you cannot cancel an order within the app, you have to log into the website separately to do that, and it doesn't play well with Apple Keychain.

What's the point of even having the app if you must log into a website for critical functions?

title: Too focused on everyone using every feature
body:
This new Home screen (Ã¢â‚¬Å“TodayÃ¢â‚¬Â) tab is too much. IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m just trying to meditate and get on with my dayÃ¢â‚¬â€not spend all day interacting with Headspace.

I do unguided sessions a few days a week, and those donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t show up in the Today tabÃ¢â‚¬Â¦or even the Meditate tab. I now have to search for Unguided sessions every. single. time. It used to be one tap from the Home screen. 

It would be nice if there were a way to opt out of seeing all the videos and soundscapes and playlists. Clearly others find value in them, but itÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s such a bummer that the original focus of this app keeps getting pushed to the side. Just let me quickly do what I want and get back to living my life away from my phone. Headspace has helped me sooooo much, but I should never have to have the app open more than 20 minutes a day. It feels like they keep adding roadblocks.

title: Terrible customer service!
body: The doctor and people you speak with on the phone are nice, but I have had the hardest time getting issues resolved. I needed a doctors note for a life insurance application, it took 5 WEEKS to get a very simple note (after calling every few days asking about it). Now I have a billing issue and I have called and emailed for 5 WEEKS now and billing has not gotten back to me after contacting them 6 times about it. There is no number for billing so I canÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t get in contact with them directly.  The convenience of having a doctor come to your house does not outweigh how much time IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢ve spent dealing with other issues. I do not recommend this service.

Way, way disappointed and it has taken a toll on a practice I have come to rely on because of the clarity in instruction from the Alo moves instructors. title: Location access and bluetooth issues
body: Tile works pretty well, but the app has quite some issues. First, it keeps asking for location access. I decided that I don't need this functionality, please stop spamming my Notification Center and throwing banners to me in the app. The second problem is more technical: bluetooth headphones do not connect automatically when receiving a phone call. Turning off bluetooth access for Tile solves this problem.

title: Greedy and repetative
body:
Cute game but it takes forever before new levels are added - if youre lucky enough to get them. My app is fully updated and yet the new levels have not reached me. I know other players have had them for weeks at this stage.

The events in the game are repetative to say the least and were recently subject to a hefty nerfing, meaning even more endless, tedious grinding is required to obtain even low-level rewards - forget about the big prices unless you have no life or a lot of money.

Recently extra tasks were invented to play in camp while waiting for new levels. While these tasks do give out some rewards, these rewards are at best boring - unless you want to pay a ridiculous amount of money for a VIP status that only lasts about three weeks. Then a new "season" will begin and you will need to pay AGAIN in order to maintain your VIP status.

All in all, the devs on this game are clearly getting lazier and greedier without even bothering to hide it anymore

title: Gets better every year
body:
I have been a member of Musixmatch for a number of year's. I enjoy the process of inputting lyrics on the off chance that they aren't already there. I enjoy syncing them in time with the music. When I feel like taking it slower I can review what others have done. If you speak another language that opens up another world for you. Ty can translate the lyrics as well! There's always something to do. On top of everything there's an academy you can take to learn everything. It's not as scary as it sounds. You earn points for everything you do and gain levels. The high your level, the greater the level of lyrics you can edit or review. If you do well enough you can become a curator and do missions which you can get paid for. It's rarely dull on Misixmatch.

Musixmatch has opened my ears to genres of music I would never listen to or given a chance on my own. Thank you Musixmatch for helping me to keep sane during this pandemic.

title: Tycoons at their finest
body: Ok I never loved idle games but this - this took the cake. One of the best games on the App Store compared to most of the garbage we see today. This symbolizes how mobile games can actually be good. Also I like the actually relevant references to recent times, for example the pandemic. I like how they added a joke there with the medicine egg. Also the variety of eggs? Rocket eggs? This takes the cake for one of the best idle games of all time. Anyways, just wanted to point out this hidden gem on the App Store. Thank you devs!

title: Excellent Info in a Beautiful, Clean Design
body:
In my quest (IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m a librarian) for an app that would display daily and monthly solar and lunar phases, I did a little research and found this one was very well-rated over and over for its breadth of data, its friendly interface, and its features. Since this app kept floating to the top, I downloaded it and I have been a Basic user for a few months.

I just love it, and I find myself using it often. It is deceptively simple, due to its clean design, but packed with information, which I enjoy browsing. Some practical uses:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢  I like to know when the full moon is coming up for viewing (and sometimes to confirm a string of bizarre behavior, although that seems to have ramped up to Ã¢â‚¬Å“dailyÃ¢â‚¬Â in 2020). 

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢  When weÃ¢â‚¬â„¢re working in the yard, itÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s great to see how much daylight we have left. 

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢  When weÃ¢â‚¬â„¢re traveling and want to view a sunrise or a sunset, we can see the time for that, no matter where we are in the world. 

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢  I have a daily alert set for dusk, to remind me to bring in our suet and birdfeeders, before they are accosted by marauding raccoons from the woods. 

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢  The app is also a terrific learning tool, both for us, ourselves, and for us to use as we help introduce our 3-year-old granddaughter to these natural, ancient rhythms and phases. 

Very pleased - a great app. I plan on upgrading for more personal tinkering and preferences. Highly recommend!

title: Fantastic app!
body:
This is a brilliant app. I rely on it when my baby brain fails me Ã°Å¸Ëœâ€š I've used it from day 1 and my daughter is now 15 weeks old. I find it especially useful for tracking breastfeeding. Only one thing could improve this app which would be an integrated "daily" chart which shows everything (feeds, sleeps, nappies etc) all in one chart rather than separate.

Edited to match the latest update - I dislike the feature how you change the date and time now, I prefer the one where you just scroll up or down.. Also it's really annoying how the "timers" are now below the "time since". It keeps confusing me. Please put timers back at the top of the home page. Thanks.

title: Finding my lost family
body:
My parents were killed in a car accident 3 weeks after the Missionaires baptized our family of 7 at the Grennich Stake Center in Sydney,Australia. An Aunt in the USA came over to Australia, picked up us five remaining kids and joined them with her five boys in Terra Linda California. Since that time I have served in numerous church callings including ten years as a Counselor in a Stake Presidency, and ten years as Stake President. I have finally found the time to find and research my family tree, and find my Mom and Dads families. You have made it so easy for me. Thank you, for helping me find my way home.

Pete Shields
Las Vegas Nevada

title: Best. Game. Ever.
body:
Ok, so one day my brother got this new game and I thought nothing of this game at the time. I thought it had a funny name and it must have been pretty dumb for it to have the name Hay Day. Then my grandpa got this game and it was all they ever talked about. Soon after I had to know why they loved this game so much, so I downloaded it. I loved it! It had awesome stuff. I was super exited when I got Tom, but I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t like that he costs so much for 1 day and takes naps in between. I bought the farm pass for 4.99 and loved it. I donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t like how most of the buildings cost so much and take so long to complete. IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m on level 19 and I canÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t wait to go further. Thanks for reading!

P.S. To the Supercell people, can you make it where stuff doesnÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t cost too much. I know thatÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s how you make money, but it would make everything a little easier. Also, can you add more variety, like make it easier to buy stuff from other farmers, and maybe add like a search bar where you can search for the item you need without having to pay Tom a lot for only one errand. I love this game and IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢d love it even more if you would consider these things. Thank you again for reading! Have a good day and a very merry Christmas!

Ok, so I just got to the level where I can get cats and... I have 8 cats at home (and 2 dogs and a tortoise). Great network and coverage, zero dead spots both inside and around the perimeter of my house.

DonÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t agree about paying for the data usage details.  That should be included!

I also want to be able to pin a device to a particular eero,if itÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s online, and only have it flip to another if it has to.  Sometimes devices connect to a further eero and the signal strength is not as good.  Especially streaming devices.

title: Make sure you have bags of cash
body:
I played this game on and off for 2 years. I took it back up after a period of 1 year and it was nothing like how I remembered. It used to be about skill. The algorithm for selecting players for matches are bad. Several players spend hundreds or thousands of dollars to get buffed robots and titans. There are far too many weapon choices and robot with barely any map or game type additions made.
This game represents everything that is wrong with the mobile gaming industry these days. In order to keep earning more, they make stuff to make noobs spend more money rather than making it about skills.

body: Lyft used to be a really good company. They were very considerate and helpful. After the pandemic hits, Lyft system is getting nasty by assigning ridiculous pick-ups to hurt the driversÃ¢â‚¬â„¢ earning and acceptance rate. Lyft will always assign drivers a far pick-up location even you are in a dense and busy area. It forces you to decline those requests and hurt your acceptance rate. It makes no sense to accept a far pick-up since you will immediately get a closer pick-up after youÃ¢â‚¬â„¢ve rejected the ridiculous one request.

title: What A Shame

This one oversteps the mark with the frequency.. so you end up watching an ad approx every one minute..  Lost me and all of my ad watching as it is just too frequent... developers note: greed loses your customer all together, so instead of watching some ads you have gotten paid for, I now watch NONE so you get nothing...bye bye
